Had caviar brunch, olives, Brussels sprouts, and cheese wheel...everything was fresh, filling, full of flavor. Very unique flavor experience for us but totally worth it!  Excellent service too!

We went in strictly to have a champagne flight. The flight was delicious, however when we went to pay the waitress said we HAD to purchase food or a snack in order for them to not lose their license during Covid. I wouldn't have minded this if they would have had a sign posted or mentioned it in the beginning, not as we are ready to leave. We ended up paying $2 for a small bowl of "complimentary" popcorn so we could be on our way instead of uncomfortably trying to look at the menu to order something so we didn't want.
I've been waiting to visit. Great wine selection!

My new, favorite, private happy place! The servers are friendly, and the owners are phenomenal! Truly! I will always come back here wirh my friends. This is a renovated home made into a wine bar / dessert oasis. Desserts are beyond-words good, and the drinks are liquid art with tastebud tantelizers. A local New Orleans born and raised bar tender, at a different location, recommended Effervessence to me and my husband.  The local bartender was on point with his recommendation. At the back of the house is a beautifully lit courtyard with a waterfeature that had the sound of babbling water. The glow of outdoor lights along with  comforting heater and firepit make the perfect ambiance. As far as desserts go, get the peanut butter cream puff with dark chocolate ganoche, and other highlyrecommended dessert was the blood orange something-or-other with whip that was to-die for. Seriously, I should keep this place secret and to myself, but it's just too good of a hospitable delight. I will not miss an oppurtunity to come here every time I visit NOLA!
A great little oasis on Rampart. People are always friendly
Excellent. Great service, good selection and lovely environment. Great spot.

Food is literally amazing! Ready to take your taste buds on an adventure of bliss?? Please check this place out. Atmosphere is a whole vibe and the staff is attentive, knowledgeable and personable. Enjoyed every single second.

A beautiful space far away from the Bourbon Street experience. Non pretentious but classy. Chill and relaxing. Kick back, order some bites and a bubbly flight.  Enjoy the service.  Enjoy the ambiance. Highly recommend

Compliments to the chef. We went expecting great champagne, and left saying we had just eaten one of the top 5 meals of our life. If you are the type of person who frequently says things like "those cocoa nibs really add to the overall flavor profile of the dish," or "that savory just keeps going and going," then you should definitely give this place a try.

Fantastic experience overall! Went here with my wife, we are from Houston. Very large selection of all the best sparkling wines, very good selection of regular wines, and the food was absolutely delicious. Will definitely come back to this place. The quality is worth the price.

lovely place. very quaint but super fun. I hear they have saints football parties :) love NOLA and this restaurant/upscale bar!

this was hands down the best discovery of my time in New Orleans. every single glass of sparkling i had tasted like the first from a bottle. and the fact that i could get half glasses meant i could try twice as many (including three BRITISH bruts that were absolutely amazing).  the glassware was beautiful, the decor perfect, staff friendly and knowledgeable, and the food was great. i had a crab and satsuma salad with ravigotte and a local sourdough type bread (their description for a naïve traveler) with some excellent butter. i had to go twice to make sure i didn't miss a single glass i wanted to try  this is a must try for any visit, and if you're a local you're wasting precious time reading this

I am not a champagne connoisseur. This restaurant was perfect for introducing me to different types of sparkling wines from different regions. The tasting flights are great. The small plates were fresh and delicious. Everything went well with the drinks. I felt it was all fairly priced. If you are looking for a unique dining experience in New Orleans, this place is definitely worth checking out.
Loved this place! Large selection of champagne and great food

Went for movie night. I have only been once before..as someone who has worked in the wine industry I appreciate the selection but not the price. The service was so so. Maybe bc movie nights can be awkward? The cheese wheel I got for $18 was lack luster. Will not be back anytime soon if at all. Hopefully tourism will keep this place afloat.
Great experience. Interesting selections and wonderful service. (Get all the popcorn!)
Loved it and the songstress Carmen was amazing
Amazing food. Amazing. Try the pomme frites. Delicious champagne. Service was top notch.

My most FAVORITE PLACE
Great experience...the owner greeted us and engaged in conversation.  Intimate setting and a wonderful list of champagne / sparkling wines.  Go by while in Nola .

I really love this bar and wish New Orleans had more places like it.  I live a few miles away, and I find myself here every couple of months.  Is it dirt cheap?  Nope, but I think it's very fairly priced for the atmosphere and quality of experience.  Their food menu also features some really delicious stuff, so be sure to come hungry! If you're a tourist, be sure to stop in, and explore other spots on Rampart!
A snazzy place to spend a Sunday afternoon from 2:30 to 5:30 when they have excellent local live jazz and specials on bottles of wine and champagne.
Great service and wine. Good music.
We visited here for the Lillet Your Way event. I am interested to return and try the restaurant at some point in the future. The cocktail event was very enjoyable.
Great service.   Very friendly.
Wish they had outdoor seating.  Specials are nice.  Food is tasty.

Beautiful place to share with friends and learn about different champagnes.  Very empress with the food pairing with the champagne.
LOVE LOVE LOVE

After a long weekend in New Orleans (my first time there), my wife and I decided to try Effervescence for our last meal before heading to the airport.  We were absolutely blown away by the place, it was perfect from beginning to end!  The restaurant is stunningly beautiful and the owner greeted us with such warm hospitality.  The bar program is truly top notch, which is hard to say in a big drinking city like NOLA, but we were left slackjawed by the quality of the food!  The owner explained that the kitchen is run by a couple who have cut their teeth in Michelin-starred restaurants out west and abroad, and their experience really shines through, along with their creativity.  My wife and I are huge seafood fans and have spent way too much money on meals in NYC and other major cities, and we consider the food here second-to-none!  Each dish was so deliberately composed with depths of flavors that would open up with each bite.  In our seafood plateau, there wasn't a single dish or element that wasn't thoughtfully put together and my wife and I were left unable to figure out which dish we enjoyed the most!  But holy cow, the fried softshell crab and avocado lettuce wrap made my eyes  roll backward, as it was easily the best fried softshell crab I've ever eaten!  During our first experience at Effervescence, I cannot find a single thing to fault as the execution of the staff, bar and kitchen was perfect.  I mean perfect.  The warmth of Crystal and Evan (one of the two chefs in the back) has left me with the most charmed memories of our experience and we can't wait to come back to New Orleans for another go!  Crystal, if you're reading this, PLEASE keep up the amazing work and I'll see you once you get your James Beard Award or your first Michelin star, whichever comes first!  :D
Absolutely delicious food! Staff was amazing! So accommodating and friendly!
